    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-19T20:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-19T20:56:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/10–1954: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 355<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d355fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_RWS1"
                            >Robertson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-19T20:56:00-05:00"
                            >October 19, 1954—8:56 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 1. Eyes only for Secretary to be
                    delivered immediately upon arrival<note n="2" xml:id="d355fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> was in Paris Oct. 20–23; see
                            <ref target="#d350fn5">footnote 5, Document 350</ref>.</note> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>. Had highly gratifying
                    conversation with Senator <persName>George</persName>. He will support you and
                    agrees that in view all circumstances negotiation treaty desirable move. In
                    absence discussions with other Democratic members committee said he of course
                    could not speak for them but in his opinion all would go along.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion pertaining to prospective Senate ratification of the
                    Manila Pact.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
